'''Dayotchanculle Oswald Upamecano''' ({{IPA|fr|upamekano|lang}}; born 27 October 1998) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

==Early life==
Dayotchanculle Oswald Upamecano<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce44/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |title=Squad List: FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022: France (FRA) |publisher=FIFA |page=12 |date=18 December 2022 |access-date=26 August 2024 |archive-date=15 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115074706/https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce44/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |url-status=live }}</ref> was born on 27 October 1998<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/222793/dayot-upamecano |title=Dayot Upamecano: Overview |publisher=ESPN |access-date=6 September 2021 |archive-date=15 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220715022455/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/222793/Dayot-Upamecano |url-status=live }}</ref> in [[Évreux]], Eure,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur56597.html |title=Dayot Upamecano |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=15 November 2022 |language=fr |archive-date=9 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509232320/http://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur56597.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and is of [[Bissau-Guinean]] descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/africa-cup-of-nations/story/4176956/africas-if-only-kids-starlets-who-could-have-played-at-afcon-instead-of-the-nations-league |title=Africa's If Only kids Starlets who could have played at Afcon instead of the Nations League |first=Colin |last=Udoh |publisher=ESPN |date=9 September 2020 |access-date=15 November 2022 |archive-date=15 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221115223017/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/africa-cup-of-nations/story/4176956/africas-if-only-kids-starlets-who-could-have-played-at-afcon-instead-of-the-nations-league |url-status=live }}</ref> He was raised in [[La Madeleine-de-Nonancourt|La Madeleine]], a neighbourhood with many African immigrants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leprogres.fr/sports/2017/11/21/dayot-upamecano-l-autre-francais-de-leipzig|title=Dayot Upamecano, l'autre Français de Leipzig|website=leprogres.fr|access-date=6 May 2018|archive-date=24 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171124140732/http://www.leprogres.fr/sports/2017/11/21/dayot-upamecano-l-autre-francais-de-leipzig|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="sofoot1" /> He was named after his great-grandfather, who was king of the village on the island of [[Jeta (Guinea-Bissau)|Jeta]] in Guinea-Bissau, where his parents are from.<ref name="ff1" /> His mother is Senegalese.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Camara |first=Mouhamed |date=2022-08-15 |title=Upamecano, défenseur Bayern : "J'ai beaucoup parlé du Sénégal avec Sadio Mané" |url=https://www.senenews.com/actualites/upamecano-defenseur-bayern-jai-beaucoup-parle-du-senegal-avec-sadio-mane_413275.html |access-date=2023-12-19 |website=Senenews - Actualité au Sénégal, Politique, Économie, Sport |language=fr-FR |archive-date=19 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231219092805/https://www.senenews.com/actualites/upamecano-defenseur-bayern-jai-beaucoup-parle-du-senegal-avec-sadio-mane_413275.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He is the first son after four daughters, and has one younger brother.<ref name="sofoot1">{{cite news |last1=Jucha |first1=Nicolas |title=Dayot Upamecano: J'ai toujours eu un corps d'adulte |url=https://www.sofoot.com/dayot-upamecano-j-ai-toujours-eu-un-corps-d-adulte-465944.html |work=SOFOOT.com |date=2 March 2019 |language=fr}}</ref> He acquired [[French nationality law|French nationality]] on 19 November 2002, through the collective effect of his mother's [[naturalization]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=JORF n° 0270 du 20 novembre 2002 - Légifrance |url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jorf/jo/id/JORFCONT000000006231 |access-date=2023-12-19 |website=legifrance.gouv.fr |page=19203 |language=fr |format=PDF |archive-date=19 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231219100104/https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jorf/jo/id/JORFCONT000000006231 |url-status=live }}</ref> As a 15-year-old, he followed [[Speech–language pathology|speech therapy sessions]] to overcome [[dyslexia]] and [[stuttering]] disorders, which caused shyness and certain difficulties in expressing himself.<ref name="ff1">{{cite news |last1=Crépin |first1=Timothé |title=Dayot Upamecano (RB Leipzig), la douce puissance |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/news/Dayot-upamecano-rb-leipzig-la-douce-puissance/1134813 |work=France Football |date=15 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220422130457/https://www.francefootball.fr/news/Dayot-upamecano-rb-leipzig-la-douce-puissance/1134813#federation=archive.wikiwix.com |archive-date=22 April 2022 |language=fr |access-date=2 April 2022 |url-status= live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Upamecano began playing football with local club [[Évreux FC 27|Évreux]], alongside the likes of [[Ousmane Dembélé]], [[Rafik Guitane]] and [[Samuel Grandsir]].<ref name="sofoot1" /> He covered a variety of positions in his youth, before being fixed on the [[centre-back]] position.<ref name="sofoot1" /> He joined the youth academy of [[Valenciennes FC|Valenciennes]] in 2013.<ref name="auto"/> Described during the time as a youth in an adult body, Upamecano shaped his play after [[Sergio Ramos]], and developed into a physically imposing defender.<ref name="sofoot1" />

===Red Bull Salzburg===
[[File:ÖFB-Cup Halbfinale FC RB Salzburg gegen FK Austria Wien 04.JPG|thumb|upright|Upamecano with [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in 2016]]

After attracting the attention of a number of major European clubs, Upamecano joined [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in July 2015 for a reported fee of €2.2 million.<ref>{{cite news|title=Manchester United target Dayot Upamecano signs for FC Red Bull Salzburg|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/manchester-united-target-dayot-upamecano-signs-fc-red-bull-salzburg-1510417|work=International Business Times|date=11 July 2015|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923183331/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/manchester-united-target-dayot-upamecano-signs-fc-red-bull-salzburg-1510417|url-status=live}}</ref> He was an unused substitute in Red Bull's [[UEFA Champions League]] game against [[Malmö FF]] on 29 July 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Red Bull Salzburg 2–0 Malmö FF |url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/champions-league/2015-2016/red-bull-salzburg-malmo-ff_mtc784130/live.shtml |publisher=Eurosport |access-date=23 September 2015 |archive-date=23 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923174900/http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/champions-league/2015-2016/red-bull-salzburg-malmo-ff_mtc784130/live.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his professional debut for Red Bull's farm team, [[FC Liefering]], two days later, in a 2–1 league win against [[SKN St. Pölten|St. Pölten]].<ref>{{cite news|title=FC Liefering gewinnt zu neunt gegen St. Pölten|url=http://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/fc-liefering/news/saison_2015_16/fc-liefering-gewinnt-zu-neunt-gegen-st.poelten.html|language=de|publisher=FC Red Bull Salzburg|date=31 July 2015|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923183314/http://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/fc-liefering/news/saison_2015_16/fc-liefering-gewinnt-zu-neunt-gegen-st.poelten.html|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 March 2016, he made his league debut with Red Bull Salzburg in a 2–1 win over [[SV Mattersburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/03/19/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/sportverein-mattersburg/2047016/ |title=Salzburg 2–1 Mattersburg |website=Soccerway |date=19 March 2016 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=7 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407144637/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/03/19/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/sportverein-mattersburg/2047016/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the first half of the 2016–17 season, Upamecano earned a regular place with the first team in both league and [[2016–17 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://de.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0252-0cda47be1036-5984148c4806-1000--europas-wunderkinder-dayot-upamecano/ |title=Europas Wunderkinder: Dayot Upamecano |publisher=UEFA |language=German |date=13 January 2017 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=31 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531040032/https://de.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0252-0cda47be1036-5984148c4806-1000--europas-wunderkinder-dayot-upamecano/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===RB Leipzig===
On 13 January 2017, Upamecano joined [[RB Leipzig]] on a {{frac|4|1|2}}-year deal, for a reported €10 million fee.<ref>{{cite web|title=RB Leipzig sign Dayot Upamecano from Red Bull Salzburg|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2017/01/13/31498772/rb-leipzig-win-race-for-barcelona-target-upamecano|website=Goal.com|date=13 January 2017|access-date=14 January 2017|archive-date=16 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116100211/http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2017/01/13/31498772/rb-leipzig-win-race-for-barcelona-target-upamecano|url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 February 2017, he made his [[Bundesliga]] debut under coach [[Ralph Hasenhüttl]] in a 1–0 defeat against [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref name="auto">{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/dayot-upamecano-rb-leipzig-france-wonderkid-centre-back-510015.jsp |title=Dayot Upamecano: The RB Leipzig defender with the world at his assured feet |publisher=Bundesliga |date=2018 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=4 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404221451/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/dayot-upamecano-rb-leipzig-france-wonderkid-centre-back-510015.jsp |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 13 September 2017, he made his [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 1–1 draw against [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2021599--leipzig-vs-monaco/?awc=15387_1613275483_e924269dd6f8053cbe06599dc2ee3374 |title=Leipzig 1–1 Monaco |publisher=UEFA |date=2018 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=4 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404235318/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2021599--leipzig-vs-monaco/?awc=15387_1613275483_e924269dd6f8053cbe06599dc2ee3374 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 February 2018, he scored his first goal in a 2–0 win over [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sky.de/fussball/rb-leipzig-vs-augsburg/spielbericht/377707 |title=Verdienter Erfolg von RB gegen Augsburg |website=Sky Sport |language=German |date=10 February 2018 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=5 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405053626/https://sport.sky.de/fussball/rb-leipzig-vs-augsburg/spielbericht/377707 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 2 July 2018, he was shortlisted for the 2018 [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] award.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/golden-boy-2018-nominees-pulisic-mckennie-havertz-lovren-isak-509451.jsp |title=Pulisic, Upamecano and more: Meet the Bundesliga's 5 Golden Boy nominations for 2018 |publisher=Bundesliga |date=2018 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718170408/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/golden-boy-2018-nominees-pulisic-mckennie-havertz-lovren-isak-509451.jsp |url-status=dead }}</ref>

On 31 July 2020, Upamecano signed a new deal until 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/740111/arsenal-dealt-major-transfer-upamecano-new-rb-leipzig-contract/|title=Arsenal dealt major blow as transfer target signs new RB Leipzig contract|website=Talksport|date=31 July 2020|access-date=1 September 2020|archive-date=5 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405120039/https://talksport.com/football/740111/arsenal-dealt-major-transfer-upamecano-new-rb-leipzig-contract/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the 2019–20 season, he reached with RB Leipzig the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] semi-finals under coach [[Julian Nagelsmann]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/rb-leipzig-psg-champions-league-live-line-ups-stats-neymar-mbappe-upamecano-12433 |title=RB Leipzig 0–3 Paris Saint-Germain UEFA Champions League semi-final: as it happened! |publisher=Bundesliga |date=2020 |access-date=16 April 2024 |archive-date=2 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241202173539/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/rb-leipzig-psg-champions-league-live-line-ups-stats-neymar-mbappe-upamecano-12433 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
On 14 February 2021, [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] announced an agreement for the signing of Upamecano on a five-year deal, to be effective as of 1 July 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2021/02/fc-bayern-sign-dayot-upamecano |title=FC Bayern sign Dayot Upamecano |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=14 February 2021 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=4 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404221451/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2021/02/fc-bayern-sign-dayot-upamecano |url-status=live }}</ref> The club reportedly met his release clause from Leipzig, set at €42.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/upamecanos-425m-release-clause-confirmed-with-bayern-target/l4pgfp25byj11p0kcrk9plqip |title=Upamecano's €42.5m release clause confirmed with Bayern target to choose between Bundesliga and Premier League |website=Goal.com |date=31 January 2021 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=28 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628182842/https://www.goal.com/en/news/upamecanos-425m-release-clause-confirmed-with-bayern-target/l4pgfp25byj11p0kcrk9plqip |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/4314935/bayern-munich-confirm-dayot-upamecano-signing |title=Bayern Munich confirm Dayot Upamecano signing |publisher=ESPN |date=14 February 2021 |access-date=14 February 2021 |archive-date=7 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211107180337/https://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/4314935/bayern-munich-confirm-dayot-upamecano-signing |url-status=live }}</ref> Upamecano's first game as a Bayern player came in a [[pre-season friendly]] on 16 July 2021 against fellow Bundesliga side [[1. FC Köln]] that saw Bayern lose 3–2 after fielding a side largely consisting of reserve and youth players.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bayern boss Nagelsmann won't panic over transfer activity|url=https://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/bayern-boss-nagelsmann-wont-panic-over-transfer-activity/1sbqitt98p46x1gvnca522l53k|access-date=23 July 2021|website=Goal.com|archive-date=5 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230405133950/https://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/bayern-boss-nagelsmann-wont-panic-over-transfer-activity/1sbqitt98p46x1gvnca522l53k|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=18 July 2021|title=Dayot Upamecano had "good feelings" during his Bayern Munich debut in 3–2 friendly loss vs. FC Koln|url=https://www.bavarianfootballworks.com/2021/7/18/22581798/bayern-munich-fc-koln-friendly-dayot-upamecano-performance-pleased-julian-nagelsmann-omar-richards|access-date=23 July 2021|website=Bavarian Football Works|archive-date=6 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406033106/https://www.bavarianfootballworks.com/2021/7/18/22581798/bayern-munich-fc-koln-friendly-dayot-upamecano-performance-pleased-julian-nagelsmann-omar-richards|url-status=live}}</ref>

He made his competitive debut on the opening day of the [[2021–22 Bundesliga|2021–22 Bundesliga season]], starting at centre-back alongside [[Niklas Süle]] in a 1–1 away draw against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lewandowski sets opening-day record |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58206961 |work=BBC Sport |date=13 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210813205117/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58206961 |archive-date=13 August 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 4–0 win over [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on 17 December, heading in a cross from [[Thomas Müller]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lewandowski breaks Muller goals record |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59702618 |work=BBC Sport |date=17 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219205240/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59702618 |archive-date=19 December 2021}}</ref>
[[File:FC RB Salzburg gegen FC Bayern München (2026-01-06 Testspiel) 19.jpg|thumb|354x354px|Upamecano with [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in 2026]]
During the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League]], Bayern defeated Upamecano's France compatriot [[Kylian Mbappé]]'s [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in the round of 16,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/1389999/dayot-upamecano-kylian-mbappe-erling-haaland-bayern-munich-man-city-champions-league/ |title='Best in the world' – Dayot Upamecano will take inspiration from win over Kylian Mbappe when facing Erling Haaland as Bayern Munich and Man City clash in Champions League |publisher=talkSPORT |date=10 April 2023 |access-date=14 July 2023 |archive-date=14 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714152118/https://talksport.com/football/1389999/dayot-upamecano-kylian-mbappe-erling-haaland-bayern-munich-man-city-champions-league/ |url-status=live }}</ref> only for them to be eliminated by a 4–1 defeat on aggregate to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the quarter-finals, in which Upamecano's performances were heavily criticised.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/bayern-munich-player-ratings-manchester-city/blt585b78b79eea80e8#cs0b9f03e59383dab9 |title=Bayern Munich player ratings vs Manchester City: An absolute disaster-class from Dayot Upamecano! |publisher=Goal.com |date=19 April 2023 |access-date=14 July 2023 |archive-date=14 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230714152116/https://www.goal.com/en/lists/bayern-munich-player-ratings-manchester-city/blt585b78b79eea80e8#cs0b9f03e59383dab9 |url-status=live }}</ref> Due to this, a [[beIN SPORTS]]' Arabic commentator referred to Upamecano as "Upamaguire" (this being due to [[Harry Maguire|Harry Maguire's]] poor form at the time).<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-03-23 |title=Dayot Upamecano called 'Upamaguire' by commentator after horrow show vs Man City |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/dayot-upamecano-called-upamaguire-by-commentator-after-horrow-show-vs-man-city-37259934 |access-date=2025-03-23 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref>

On 4 November 2023, he scored his first goal of the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]] in the fourth minute of a 4–0 away win over Borussia Dortmund.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/profis/bundesliga/2023-2024/borussia-dortmund-fc-bayern-muenchen-04-11-2023/spielbericht | title = Starke Bayern triumphieren im Klassiker beim BVB | website = FC Bayern Munich | language = de | date = 4 November 2023 | access-date = 4 November 2023 | archive-date = 1 December 2023 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20231201232516/https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/profis/bundesliga/2023-2024/borussia-dortmund-fc-bayern-muenchen-04-11-2023/spielbericht | url-status = live }}</ref> In February 2024, Upamecano was sent off twice in the span of four days: on 14 February, he received his first straight red card in the Champions League during the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|round of 16]] first leg away match against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]], which resulted in a penalty kick and a 1–0 defeat;<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68317673 |title=Dayot Upamecano: Bayern Munich defender condemns racist abuse after Lazio defeat |publisher=BBC Sport |date=16 February 2024 |access-date=18 February 2024 |archive-date=6 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240706024713/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68317673 |url-status=live }}</ref> on 18 February, he received two yellow cards and again conceded a penalty in a 3–2 loss to [[VfL Bochum|Bochum]] in the Bundesliga.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68332112 |title=VfL Bochum 1848 3–2 Bayern Munich |publisher=BBC Sport |date=18 February 2024 |access-date=18 February 2024 |archive-date=18 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240218190344/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68332112 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Under new manager [[Vincent Kompany]]'s coaching, Upamecano's performances improved drastically, as he helped Bayern reclaim the [[2024–25 Bundesliga]] title.<ref>{{Cite web |title=How Dayot Upamecano transformed into Bayern Munich's Mr. Reliable |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/how-dayot-upamecano-transformed-into-bayern-munich-s-mr-reliable-31031 |access-date=2025-11-07 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref> On 13 February 2026, he extended his contract with the club until 2030.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2026/02/dayot-upamecano-extends-with-bayern-to-2030 |title=Dayot Upamecano signs new contract with FC Bayern |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=13 February 2026 }}</ref> Two months later, on 28 April, he scored his first Champions League goal in a 5–4 away defeat against Paris Saint-Germain in the competition's [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|semi-final]] first leg.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/02a4-207ffc37742f-abe4807faa3d-1000--paris-5-4-bayern-highlights-holders-edge-epic-champions-le/ |title=Paris 5-4 Bayern highlights: Holders edge epic Champions League semi-final first leg |publisher=UEFA |date=28 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Upamecano played for the [[France national under-16 football team|France under-16]] team that finished third in the 2014 Aegean Cup.<ref name=Sky>{{cite news|title=Dayot Upamecano: Who is the Man Utd, Man City and Arsenal target?|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/9873037/dayot-upamecano-who-is-the-man-utd-man-city-and-arsenal-target|publisher=Sky Sports|date=2 June 2015|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923181614/http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/9873037/dayot-upamecano-who-is-the-man-utd-man-city-and-arsenal-target|url-status=live}}</ref> He played in three of his country's four games and was named the competition's best defender.<ref name=FFF>{{cite news|title=Dayot Upamecano|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2543561904-dayot-upamecano|language=fr|publisher=French Football Federation|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=12 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140152/https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2543561904-dayot-upamecano|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=USA win 2014 Mercedes-Benz Aegean Cup|url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=471&ftxtID=19837|publisher=Turkish Football Federation|date=26 January 2014|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923194722/http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=471&ftxtID=19837|url-status=live}}</ref> He subsequently moved up to the [[France national under-17 football team|France under-17]] squad, making his debut in a [[2015 UEFA European Under-17 Championship qualification|European Championship qualifier]] against Cyprus on 27 October 2014.<ref name=FFF/> France won the [[2015 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]], with Upamecano playing in all six of his country's matches and being named in the team of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |title=Dayot Upamecano|url= https://www.uefa.com/under17/teams/players/250079545--dayot-upamecano/ |publisher=UEFA |access-date=23 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Team of the Tournament|url= http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2015/technical-report/uefa-technical-team/index.html |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150729224331/http://www.uefa.com/under17/season=2015/technical-report/uefa-technical-team/index.html |url-status= dead |archive-date= 29 July 2015 |publisher=UEFA|access-date=23 September 2015}}</ref> He debuted for [[France national under-18 football team|France under-18]] in a 0–0 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] draw with [[United States men's national under-18 soccer team|United States under-18]] on 4 September 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=France – Etats-Unis|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/8/u18/matchs/2173/2015-09-04/france-etats-unis|language=fr|publisher=French Football Federation|access-date=23 September 2015|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923180509/https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/8/u18/matchs/2173/2015-09-04/france-etats-unis|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 5 September 2020, Upamecano debuted for the [[France national football team|French senior squad]], starting in a [[UEFA Nations League]] group stage match against [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Victor|last=Laspière|title=Ligue des nations : la France domine la Suède (1-0) grâce à un but de Kylian Mbappé|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france-suivez-en-direct-france-suede-1599153407|website=[[France Bleu]]|date=5 September 2020|language=fr|archive-date=15 June 2024|access-date=15 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240615114149/https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france-suivez-en-direct-france-suede-1599153407|url-status=live}}</ref> Three days later on 8 September, he scored his first international goal in a 4–2 victory against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=France – Croatie: Les Bleus disposent de la Croatie dans un match riche en buts|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/equipe-de-france/france-croatie-les-bleus-disposent-de-la-croatie-dans-un-match-riche-en-buts-6965890|website=[[Ouest-France]]|date=8 September 2020|language=fr|access-date=15 June 2024|archive-date=15 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240615114149/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/equipe-de-france/france-croatie-les-bleus-disposent-de-la-croatie-dans-un-match-riche-en-buts-6965890|url-status=live}}</ref>

Upamecano played a pivotal role in France's [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], starting five of France's seven matches.{{Citation needed|date=January 2023}} This included playing the entire 120 minutes in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup Final|final]] in an eventual 3–3 loss in penalties to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Argentina-France Line-ups|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285077/400128145?country=US&wtw-filter=ALL|publisher=FIFA|date=18 December 2022|access-date=20 December 2022|archive-date=23 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323133335/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285077/400128145?country=US&wtw-filter=ALL|url-status=live}}</ref>

